 Congress read this letter on 6 April (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Worthington Chauncey Ford et al., eds. &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Continental Congress, 1774-1789&lt;/i&gt;. 34 vols. Washington, D.C., 190437. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">JCC</span></span>, 4:260).</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0409-0001-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0409-0001-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>The previous Saturday was 23 March.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0409-0001-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0409-0001-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0414" class="document">General Orders, 28 Mar. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0409-0001-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0409-0001-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>See enclosure printed as an appendix to this document.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0409-0001-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0409-0001-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>See Petition from Inhabitants of Nova Scotia, 8 Feb. 1776.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0409-0001-fn-0005-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0409-0001-fn-0005">5</a>
	
   <p>For a discussion of Jonathan Eddys and John Allans attempts to lead expeditions to Nova Scotia, see a <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0192&amp;expandNote=GEWN-03-03-02-0192-sn#GEWN-03-03-02-0192-sn" class="document">Citizen of Nova Scotia to GW, 8 Feb. 1776, source note</a>.</p>

